This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation using convolutional neural networks. The use of U-Net and Inception modules also suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of the ADAM optimizer and learning rate also suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the mention of stroke datasets and image modalities suggests that it may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
